request from us or that we believe may be of interest to you, where (if required to do so) you have consented to be contacted for such purposes unless you have opted out of receiving such information.
To manage your requests
by creating booking records and send you booking confirmations, confirmations, invoices and statuses.
To serve you targeted advertising
:
We may use your information to develop and display content and advertisements (and work with third-party vendors who do so) tailored to your interests and/or location and to measure its effectiveness.
For business transfers
We may use your information to evaluate or carry out a merger, divestiture, restructuring, reorganization, dissolution or other sale or transfer of some or all of our assets, whether as an ongoing business or as part of a bankruptcy, liquidation or similar proceeding, in which the Personal Data we hold about users of our Service is among the assets transferred.
For other purposes
,
we may use your information for other purposes, such as analyzing data, identifying usage trends, determining the effectiveness of our advertising campaigns, and evaluating and improving the Service, products, services, marketing, and experience.
To notify you
of updates
and changes to our service.
To meet
customer service requirements
and to handle complaints and feedback
We will contact you only by electronic means (e-mail or SMS) with information about updates, goods and services similar to those we have previously delivered to you. If you do not want us to use your data in this way, please let us know by contacting the Data Controller at
privacy@taxi.gr
. We may also use and analyze aggregated information (collective data related to a group or category of services or customers, from which individual customer identities or characteristics have been removed) collected through the provision of analytics so that you can manage, support, improve and grow your business.
We only work with trusted partners and authorities. We only share when there is a good reason to do so. We limit sharing to only what is required. We do not sell your personal information.
We may share your personal information in the following circumstances:
With third-party providers
to
provide the service, such as drivers and fleet operators. These will include service providers related to payment processing, warehousing, marketing companies, professionals, social media platform providers for our own marketing and research partners.
